Diagnosis
. Size large, length 
3.9–4.9 mm
; ground color of dorsum uniformly medium brownish, elytral hairs uniformly light yellow-brown, (
Fig 11
), venter medium brown; ventral tooth of profemur large (
Fig 22
); lateral margins of all ventrites entire; median lobe of male genitalia long and narrow, evenly tapered to non-incised apex (
Fig 30
).
